{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1b42c88-8f8d-44c7-8721-2e68891eb6bc","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .dmp file. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me point you in the right direction.\n\n**Tools for analyzing .NET crash dumps:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — interactive CLI tool\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the session:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **LLDB + SOS plugin** (Linux)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) — full-featured GUI debugger with SOS extension\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp`\n2. Use `pe` to print the exception that caused the crash\n3. Use `clrstack` to see the stack trace\n4. Use `threads` then `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` to inspect other threads\n\nWould you like me to help you run any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e41239d8-b3e5-42c4-88a2-b9c79c000981","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":447,"requestId":"D81A:CE960:606076C:6858510:69FBF16B"},"id":"61e3fdb0-db0c-41a2-bd40-1826de22de95","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:57:11.339Z","parentId":"5328002c-caea-40e2-8bf0-b1b322bc1d03"}
